Defendant Etty Rosado in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Anthony Jackson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: LNR  
Court ordered charge amended to Disorderly Conduct pursuant to Milwaukee County Ordinance 63.01 to which Defendant plead no contest. Court finds defendant guilty of amended charge. Case set for final pre-trial. The defendant fails to appear. The Court orders a bench warrant issued but STAYED until the next scheduled Court date. Case remains calendared for Jury trial on 3/18/2019, branch 12.

Defendant Etty Rosado in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Thaddeus P McGuire appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Pre-Trial Conference. Defense counsel has received discovery and offer and requests a Jury Trial. Court grants request.   ALL PARTIES ARE NOTIFIED AS OF JANUARY 7, 2019 CASE WILL BE REASSIGNED TO JUDGE BOROWSKI, BRANCH 12, COURTHOUSE ROOM 615.  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 21, 2019 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for March 18, 2019 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Etty Rosado in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Thaddeus P McGuire appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for Status of Counsel. Defense counsel has received discovery and offer and requests additional time to review. Court grants request. Case remains calendared in Br 45.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 17, 2018 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Etty Rosado in court.  Anthony Jackson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court conducted Indigency Hearing. Court held colloquy with defendant. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel by court. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. The court appointed Attorney Ramon Valdez to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $70.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning at the completion of the case, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Signed, Distributed & Filed, Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense. Case is adjourned for a Status of Counsel date in Branch 45.  Status conference scheduled for November 27, 2018 at 08:30 am.
